commit cb210e4a9962ee4eb0ea6d8935a2bdb026b4084d
Author: Barak Hirshberg <hirshb@carasso.usilu.net>
Date:   Fri Sep 6 13:00:32 2019 +0200

    Main change to include PIMD for Bosons.
    free_qstep() now calls get_spring_forces() for evaluation of bosonic spring forces.
    Defined get_spring_forces() which returns F which holds forces on all atoms for all replicas.
    To do so, it calls Evaluate_VB() which returns VB_j; j=1,...,N and all E_N^{(k)} needed.
    Then, get_spring_forces() loops over all beads of all atoms and calculate the force acting
    on each one. To do so, it calls Evaluate_dVB().

commit 7887dab622d599514632a19a064a8d48c0a371ab
Author: Barak Hirshberg <hirshb@carasso.usilu.net>
Date:   Thu Sep 5 12:01:59 2019 +0200

    I have made changes to free_qstep() in normalmodes.py
    For bosons, the Hamiltonian can still be separated into a free ring polymer (RP) part
    and a potential part.
    However, due to exchange symmtery, the free RP part contains more than one
    configuration and cannot be integrated analytically, as done usually for distinguishable
    particles.
    Therefore, I implemented a simple velocity verlet integrator instead.
    The bosonic forces are currently set to zero and need to be calculated still.
    
    Also, we will probably want to add the possibility to treat only some atoms as bosons
    and other as distinguishable, which is not done now.

