commit f26051ddf325dc35346619d492e4ae755cea2bc6
Author: Michele Ceriotti <ceriottm@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 12 09:33:04 2019 +0100

    Minimal mechanism to handle "unstructured outputs" from motion classes
    
    In short, the idea is to have a very simple class to create and manage output files that don't fall within the trajectory/property/checkpoint classification. The same prefix is applied, and closing and flushing is handled by a softexit trigger.
    
    * Start by sanitizing the absurd output prefix mechanism.
    No debug statements not to hurt the sensitivity of future contributors
    
    * Cleaned up code, working prefix encapsulation from the outputs I/O
    
    * Work in progress
    
    * Proof of principle for a distributed floating output mechanism.
    
    Also cleaned up a bit output infrastructure. One still needs to see how to deal with multiple systems, if needed.
    
    * Delegation for BaseOutput, and a first go at revamping the phonons example
    
    *   Starting to bring instanton branch up to date for outputs
    
    *   Just relabelling the example in order to make it understandable...
    
    *   Clean implementation. Should be safe, was tested for one example and behaves
      correctly. I left the intermediate temporary files out of this treatment since they are
      erased by the end of the simulation.
    
    * the phonons prefix is now an "infix".
    
    * Just minor tweaks - keep default lowercase for output files
    
    *   Making paths relative to folder in order to run examples.
    
    *   Lower cases default.
    
    *   Draft of a README file for the instanton example
    
    *   Further cleaning. Still needs to get removal of files from BaseOutput class.
      Too late today, something odd happening (gave up).
    
    * os.remove expects the filename
    
    * Quick-fix for using BaseOutput remove() in the instanton tools

