    A faster evaluation for library ff by avoiding threading on serial execution (#8)
    
    * A faster evaluation for library ff by avoiding threading on serial execution
    * Resuscitated the "matching" attrib for ffsocket, that had been lost!
    * A number of (attempted) optimizations. Most important 80% faster checkpoint store
    * Removed some more debugging code
    * Fixed typo in examples
    * Fixed a bug in softexit registration for non-threaded forcefields
    * Updated PLUMED interface to the latest GBussi edits
    * adapted ffquip.wq
    * REMDSORT gets simpler naming scheme that reflects whatever is chosen for the replicas
    
    * MASSIVE RESTRUCTURING OF SOCKETS!
    
    This is soooo much easier now. Still have to benchmark if and how much it makes things faster, but it's definitely easier tu understand and maintain
    
    * Removed some threadlocks that are now (probably) useless
    * Some review code merged from elsewhere, Co-Authored-By: ceriottm <ceriottm@users.noreply.github.com>
    
    * Makes default timeout for a socket interface be one hour rather than no timeout
    There can be corner cases in which a calculator gets stuck and it's probably better
    for i-PI to try and carry on rather than get stuck forever
    
    * A bit of additional cleanups. The code seems to pass all regtests.
    * Implemented here some changes that were suggested on a dead branch

