commit 8f5ae2c846e7a58ed3105a71f604e66f4eb98148
Author: Venkat Kapil <venkat.kapil@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 4 14:48:05 2018 +0100

    Feat/gleacf (#10)
    
    * Generalizes the deconvolution process to NMGLEs as well.
    * Also changed a rather confusing option for the time step to a scaling factor of time.
    * Changed the names of the options and their descriptions in argparse
    * Cleaned up the gleacf tool. Increased the verbosity of the arg parse options. Also allows one to manually provide A and C matrices. And updated the example and their READMEs.
    * raises an exception if neither the i-pi xml not the A matrix is provided.
    
    * Tested the manual version of providing the A matrix with a white noise thermostat. Also provided instructions in the README.
    * 1) States that in case of a NM_GLE only the centroid thermostat is used for the deconv as the input spectrum is assumed to come from the dynamics of the centroid.
    2) the case of langevin thermostat was extended to pile_l.
    3) throws an exception if an appropriate GLE thermostat is not found.
    
    * changed the font of command line options from big caps to small caps.

