commit bcd7ffa7d433229c2dffaa32386b87b6ca918567
Author: Michele Ceriotti <ceriottm@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 9 09:15:47 2018 +0100

    Replica exchange + metadynamics (#3)
    
    REMD+METAD implementation.
    =========================
    This requires a rather complicated input and combination with multiple PLUMED inputs, but this is not dissimilar to other implementations. It's just a technically complex methodology.
    Examples are given that should make it clear how this is set up, but probably this is one good candidate for an "advanced tutorial" in a future better_docs effort
    
    * Removed some stray calls to beads.vpath
    * Created an example with GLE thermostat
    * Rescale GLE DOFs. Should fix a bug in main
    * Added examples of different REMD scenarios
    * Include GLE and open paths
    * Use symlinks rather than copies for the (rather heavy) zundel data files
    * First implementation of selective metad execution, to implement REMD+METAD
    * Fixed a silly error in plumed input throwing uninformative segfault Should liaise with PLUMED devs to make sure errors are propagated meaningfully
    * Added a MultiSmotion so we can combine REMD and MetaD.
    * Fixed a bug that would output more and more smotion items in the multi restart
    * A simple change to the poll routine can reduce latency by a factor of 2!!!
    * Trying to speed up REMD overhead.
    * Removed some debug code. REMD is now faster with reduced latency
    * Applied style corrections addressing Ondrej's comments
    * Fixed a sync problem between i-PI an PLUMED

